        {
            "title": "Stocks bounce back from bank fears as AXP soars. S&P 500 rises to 6,650 points. Nasdaq and Dow Jones up by 0.3%. Financials rebound. Trump optimistic on US-China trade.",
            "id": "60e82474-5799-4081-a3eb-2b7e92b507e4",
            "description": "Wall Street showed resilience against credit concerns impacting bank stocks, as major indices experienced slight gains during midday trading in New York, pointing towards a positive weekly conclusion. AXP emerged as one of the top performers, with the S&P 500 climbing 0.2% to reach 6,650 points, almost offsetting losses from the previous day, while both the Nasdaq 100 and the Dow Jones saw a 0.3% uptick. Following a notable downturn on Wednesday, financials and bank stocks rebounded, with the SPDR Regional Banking ETF (NYSE: KRE) rising by 1.1% and the Financials Select Sector SPDR Fund (NYSE: XLF) showing a 0.5% increase. President Donald Trump expressed confidence in the economic relationship with China, suggesting that the proposed 100% tariff hike on Chinese goods might not be implemented. For further details, the complete article can be found on Benzinga.com.",
